 as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":19,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Sharington was born in 1363, in Crownthorpe, Norfolk, England, her father, John Sharington, was 37 and her mother, Elizabeth, was 34. She had at least 2 sons with John De Wymondham. She died in 1384, in Norfolk, England, at the age of 21."},"et":{"1363–1384":"1363–1384","1359–1415":"1359–1415","1379–1450":"1379–1450","1384–1445":"1384–1445","1326–Male":"1326–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1415":"1415","1326":"1326","1359":"1359","1379":"1379","1445":"1445","1363":"1363","1330":"1330","1384":"1384","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","Wymondham, Norfolk, England":"Wymondham, Norfolk, England","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England","Crownthorpe, Norfolk, England":"Crownthorpe, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"1363–1384":"1363–1384","1359–1415":"1359–1415","1379–1450":"1379–1450","1384–1445":"1384–1445","1326–Male":"1326–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–